events.name: Joyful Movement Program
events.date: Sundays in April, Starting 4/3, at 5pm CST
events.details: A 4 week virtual group program created to help you move your body with less rules, more joy.

events.name: Strength Training for Runners
events.details: Calling all runners who want to strength train to support their running.

events.name: Simple Strength
events.details: This 6 month kettlebell program is for movers who want to improve their kettlebell technique.

events.name: 5 Tenants of Running a Mindful & Ethical Fitness Business
events.date: 3 Week Series, Mondays in May.  5/9, 5/16, 5/23 @ 5pm CST.
events.details: Building an ethical, mindful business is more than checking boxes. It's developing and applying a mindful lens to every interaction and creating a truly inclusive environment. This course is for all coaches who want to do the work to build a mindful business.

events.name: Yoga Basics
events.details: Calling all beginners :) Yoga can be intimidating for newbies. Join me for a beginners focused class. We'll play around with the basics, and finish class with some restorative poses and meditation. Come learn with me.

events.name: Breathing Workshop
events.details: Join me for a two hour workshop on the breathing techniques we use in yoga. We'll utilize the breath to drop into the present. We'll practice a bit of asana, but the bulk of this workshop will be purely focused on the breath.

events.name: Body Image Workshop
events.date: Every Sunday in May 2022 Starting May 1st. 4pm EST.
events.details: Have you found yourself spending too much time and emotional energy being critical and picking apart your body? We live in a culture that over emphasizes what the body looks like. In this course, we will create awareness around the role that body image plays with our self-esteem and overall mental and physical health. We'll work to understand the internal and external influences that affect one's body image.

events.name: Book Club
events.details: Each month we read and discuss a book relating to the body. Join us in April for Sonya Renee Taylor's- The Body is Not an Apology.

events.name: Move with Holly
events.details: Join my online subscription platform for live HIIT, Barre, and Pilates classes. All classes are recorded and can be accessed for replay later. Joy my community, and move your body for fun. More details on my website: hollysjoy.com.

events.name: An Anti-Diet Approach to Ayurveda
events.details: Join me for a workshop on how to include Ayurveda in your life without the diet culture influence of the west.

events.name: PCOS and Nutrition
events.date: Mondays in May at 5pm, starting May 2nd
events.details: Join us for a 4-week group program. Learn everything you want to know about PCOS and nutrition, movement, stress management, hormones, supplements, and sleep hygiene.

events.name: Gardening for Nutrition
events.details: During this event we'll discuss how to effectively grow nutritious food in your summertime garden. We'll go over the fundamentals of gardening, learn which nutritious crops grow best in Middle Tennessee, and learn practical tips on how to cook your home grown produce.

userProfiles.specialties: Strength Training, Joyful Movement, Training in ED Recovery, HAES Approach to Fitness
userProfiles.bio:
Hi! I'm Lainey, a non-diet coach helping people find joy in their movement again. I work with clients 1:1 in person in Nashville, and also on Zoom. Personally, I enjoy weightlifting, dancing, trail running, and walking with my dog.

In 2020, I started the Move with Joy Program to help clients rebuild their relationship with movement. The MWJ Program runs for 5 weeks. We take a deep dive into our beliefs about movement, societal pressures around movement, diet and size, and work on building a path forward for each individual.

I'm a physical therapist, trail runner, dog lover, and movement and learning enthusiast.  I started my physical therapy practice in 2018, and my aim is to help my clients get back to the activities they love doing as soon as possible. 

I offer compassionate, educational care.

userProfiles.specialties: Hardstyle Kettlebell Training, Strength Training, Strength Training for Beginners, HAES Aligned
userProfiles.bio:
NASM CPT since 2015. I work with beginners to lifting and beginners to kettlebell training. My clients are sometimes movement enthusiasts who want to use strength training to supplement their other movement hobbies- running, yoga, climbing, etc. I also work with people who simply want to feel stronger in their day to day life, and are curious about lifting.

I focus on teaching clients how to lift, and work to make my clients feel comfortable making their own choices about their movement. I think strength training is beneficial for all humans, and I aim to make training fun by empowering my clients with the knowledge of how to lift heavy things well, encouraging their curiosity, and highlighting their swoleness :)
Inclusive and trauma mindful strength and fitness coach. CPT since 2012.

In high school, I started attending yoga classes a the Y because of my debilitating anxiety. The breath work and mindfulness techniques helped me get back to baseline. Today, I teach a mix of asana heavy vinyasa flow, and yin. I love the balance between the two practices. In my teaching, my focus on giving my students options, so they can make the best choices for their body and mental state.

I hope to make a positive impact on this world by sharing the teachings of yoga with others. I stumbled into my first yoga class in 2014, and that one class transformed my life. My life felt chaotic, but through the practice of yoga I've learned how to manage my anxiety and handle difficult situations. I hope to share yoga with those who are reluctant to try, and continue to be a better human through my own practice and study of yoga.

userProfiles.specialties: Eating Disorder, Body Image, Addiction, Trauma, Life Transitions
userProfiles.bio: LPC, MHSP. Practicing since 2015. I was drawn to this work through my own journey of self discovery. I offer clients a soft place to land, be seen and cared for.

userProfiles.specialties: Strength Training, Hardstyle Kettlebell Training, Joyful Movement for ALL Bodies
userProfiles.bio: I've been working in the wellness space as a personal trainer since 2012. I opened my gym, Phoenix Rising, in 2015. At Phoenix Rising I've worked with my community to develop a gym space that is welcoming to all skill levels and all bodies. Fitness doesn't have a look, and every client I work with has the right to be seen and coached as a whole human. We don't focus on calories burned and sweat dropped. We focus on reclaiming the space to move our bodies.

I am a motivational coach based in Portland, Oregon. I spent years working at a 9-5 desk job. In 2015, I jumped full time into the wellness space and haven't looked back. In 2020, I took my business completely online. I work with a community of people who want to move their bodies for fun. I teach a mix of barre, pilates and HIIT classes to my subscribers.

userProfiles.specialties: Hatha Yoga, Restorative Yoga, Yoga Therapy, Yoga + Social Justice
userProfiles.bio:
I began practicing yoga, with my mother, as a child. I started studying yoga at 18, and have had the deep privilege from learning from ABC Yoga Institute, Healing Arts, and the SunMoon Institute. Currently, I'm working on my Professional Yoga Therapist Certification.

I believe the culture and teachings of yoga can bring light to the disparities within the wellness space. My offering focus on the intersection between yoga and social justice.

I offer weekly community classes around the Nashville area, and also work with clients individually. Check my website for class times.

I've been a lifting enthusiast since high school, and came to physical therapy as a patient after experiencing injury in college baseball. I work with athletes and gym rats helping clients feel less pain and more gains.

userProfiles.specialties: Registered Dietitian (RDN), Nutrition Therapist, Health & Wellness Coach, Non-Diet approach to diabetes management, HAES
userProfiles.bio:
In one-on-one nutrition therapy I help clients take empowered action that leads to lifelong healthy habits. My process considers the whole person and focuses on the importance of education, development of self-care skills and introspective awareness. 

Bachelor of Science in Food & Nutrition Science from MTSU
Masters of Science in Exercise and Nutrition Science from Vanderbilt

When I'm not working you can find me, getting creative in the kitchen, swinging kettlebells, and hanging with my husband and dog.

userProfiles.specialties: Registered Dietitian Nutritionist (RDN), Nutrition Therapist, and Certified Master Gardener
userProfiles.bio:
I have a passion for bridging the worlds of gardening and nutrition to help clients discover a more dynamic understanding of food, nutrition, and health. I enjoy working with a broad range of conditions, including digestive disorders, blood pressure, cholesterol concerns, cardiovascular health, and vegetarian and vegan eating.

Bachelor of Science in Food and Nutrition from the University of Alabama

Outside of work and gardening, I'm currently training for my first marathon!

userProfiles.specialties: Licensed Clinical Mental Health Counselor, Counseling and Psychotherapy for Dealing with the Human Condition
userProfiles.bio: As a Licensed Clinical Mental Health Counselor in private practice in Knoxville, TN, it is my passion to work with individuals who are dealing with life situations that have caused them distress. I have 28 years of experience in psychology and mental health and I’ve been in private practice for fifteen years. I consider the work I do an honor and a privilege.
